column9: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Unique Users)
column10: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen through unpaid distribution. (Unique Users)
column11: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen through paid distribution such as an ad. (Unique Users)
column12: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Total Count)

column14: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen through paid distribution such as an ad. (Total Count)
column15: Lifetime: The number of unique people who engaged in certain ways with your Page post, for example by commenting on, liking, sharing, or clicking upon particular elements of the post. (Unique Users)

column3: End your #DisabilityAwareness month right and watch Symbiotic, created by Rachel Greenhoe.

Our dear friend and unofficial Parker Posey of #OTV, Darling Shear, got a lovely mention in the Windy City Times for breaking binaries in the incredibly heteronormative field of dance. 

See more of her choreographic process in #TheDarlingSeries, a docu-series by Diana Quinones Rivera, out now at http://www.weareo.tv/originals/darlingshear OR live in living color at The Fly Honey Show 9 (Aug 9 - Sept 8).

#TheDarlingSeries is a 14 episode docu-series by Diana Quinones Rivera, that follows Darling Shear as she choreographs a piece for 6 dancers rooted in the tradition of Hollywood musicals. 

See it on Monday, July 16th at Reunion Chicago! RSVP: OTV Presents: Darling Shear series & Symbiotic

"I wanted to create a queer web-series with people of color that felt honest. I wanted to see a story about a dark skin, voluptuous black woman, so I wrote episode 3. I read a lot about femme-phobia, so I wrote episode 5 that follows an effeminate gay man. I wanted to use comedy as a means to explore identity, gender, and sexuality." - Hook Ups creator Arnetta Randall for Lezbelib.com. 

Check out all 5 episodes of season one right here!

Watch #TheTTV now: http://www.weareo.tv/originals/the-t

A huge THANK YOU to our amazing partners, SLAY TV, a platform elevating narratives of queer and trans people of color through curating and creating compelling video content, and CHILL, a new quarterly magazine for urban men, for their support in making our #2QIKLIVE dreams a reality!

You can watch Derrick Woods-Morrow's The Roach Is Coming at Headmaster Magazine! Watch it online now before it goes offline in August!

"The video is an extension of Derrick’s project for Headmaster No. 8. The issue is thematically structured around the Village People, and he was asked to consider the importance of the police uniform in relation to authority. At the time, the editors had no idea that Derrick would soon be involved in a late-night altercation with the Chicago PD after leaving a gay bar, or that he would use his assignment to reconnect with a boyhood friend, now a police officer, whom he hadn’t seen in many years. The Roach Is Coming is based on a recording of the intimate conversation between Derrick and his childhood friend, recorded as Derrick and the other man bathed one another."

“Symbiotic” is a series created by Rachel Greenhoe about young queer people with invisible (and visible) disabilities trying to make their way in Chicago.

The show follows Tara and Maggie, a newly moved-in-together couple who are trying to enjoy a normal life despite the limitations caused by Tara’s autism and Maggie’s host of issues.

The series premieres this month on OTV! Stay tuned for details on the screening. #DisabilityAwarenessMonth >> Series premieres on Monday, July 16th at Reunion Chicago - RSVP here: OTV Presents: Darling Shear series & Symbiotic
